author: COMSOL
description: Microstrip filters can be fabricated directly on a printed circuit board (PCB) with a microstrip line going from the input to the output. Along the microstrip line there are a number of stubs of certain lengths and widths. The design of the filter involves choosing the impedance of the microstrip line, the impedance of the stub microstrips, and the length of the stubs. This particular filter has a seventh-pole low-pass Chebyshev response. The example uses the Electromagnetic Waves interface that solves the vector Helmholtz wave equation. The characteristics of the filter are sensitive to the placement and length of the stubs; therefore this example also analyzes the change in filter characteristics as a function of mechanical deformation.
